The purpose of this study is to compare the safety and effectiveness of fenofibrate and pravastatin in treating HIV-positive patients who have abnormal levels of fat (lipids) in the blood.

 Increased lipids in the blood associated with HIV infection and anti-HIV drugs is a growing problem.

 The drugs used in this study are known to reduce certain lipids, but little is known about their safety and effectiveness.

 This study will see if one of the drugs is safer and more effective than the other, or if combining the drugs is the safest and most effective way to lower lipids.

