 On June 26, 2001, this study was reviewed by the Data and Safety Monitoring Board (DSMB).

 The DSMB is an independent board monitoring the progress of the study.

 The review showed that neither pravastatin nor fenofibrate alone were effective in reaching all the cholesterol and triglyceride goals.

 There were no safety concerns.

 It is not known if the combination of fenofibrate and pravastatin is effective and safe.

 Therefore, it is important to continue this study.

